<refsect1 id='description'><title>DESCRIPTION</title>
<para>Run COMMAND with completely-specified CONTEXT, or with current or
transitioned security context modified by one or more of LEVEL,
ROLE, TYPE, and USER.</para>

<para>If none of <option>-c</option>, <option>-t</option>, <option>-u</option>, <option>-r</option>, or <option>-l</option>, is specified,
the first argument is used as the complete context.  Any additional
arguments after <emphasis remap='I'>COMMAND</emphasis> are interpreted as arguments to the
command.</para>

<para>Note that only carefully-chosen contexts are likely to successfully
run.</para>

<para>Run a program in a different SELinux security context.
With neither CONTEXT nor COMMAND, print the current security context.</para>

<para>Mandatory arguments to long options are mandatory for short options too.</para>
